
itools 0.50.2 (2009/01/20)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.abnf             itools.ical             itools.tmx
  itools.csv              itools.isetup           itools.uri
  itools.datatypes        itools.odf              itools.vfs
  itools.gettext          itools.pdf              itools.web
  itools.git              itools.relaxng          itools.workflow
  itools.handlers         itools.rest             itools.xapian
  itools.html             itools.rss              itools.xliff
  itools.http             itools.srx              itools.xml
  itools.i18n             itools.stl

This is, mostly, a bug fix release.

The 'merge_dics' function has been renamed to 'merge_dicts'; using
'merge_dics' still works, but it is deprecated.  The 'is_datatype'
and 'copy_datatype' functions are deprecated.

Several improvements and fixes to itools.ical and itools.pdf (PML).
A regression has been fixed in itools.web, now POST methods honor
'context.commit' again.

Now 'isetup-build.py' correctly uses the committer's datetime instead
of the author's datetime.

The bugs fixed include #512, #516 and #538.


